open clusters. That is, there is a large spread in coronal activity for
stars with v sin i {\textless} 25 km s-1, where we assume there is
an intrinsic link between increasing rotation and increasing activity
superimposed upon which are a variety of observational and physical
mechanisms that act to smear out this relation; above v sin i {\textasciitilde} 25 km
s-1, all of the low-mass stars have log
(LX/Lbol) {\textasciitilde} -3.0, the canonical ``saturation''
limit. Our measurements of the Hα equivalent widths are consistent
with a similar relationship holding for chromospheric activity. One and
