timescale appears to vary by stellar mass, ranging from {\textasciitilde}1 Myr for {\textgreater}1.3 Msolar stars to {\textasciitilde}3 Myr for {\textless}0.08 Msolar brown dwarfs. The exponential decay function may provide a useful empirical formalism for estimating very rough ages for YSO populations and for modeling the effects of disk-locking on the angular momentum of young stars.},
