assumptions which optimise irradiation effects and taking into account
the extension of the outer atmospheric layers, we still find  {\textasciitilde} 20\%
discrepancy between observed and theoretical radii. An extra source of
energy seems to be required to explain the observed value of the first
transit planet.},
