medium/high-resolution spectroscopy, adaptive optics/speckle imaging,
and archival survey images to rule out any false-positive detection
scenarios, validate the planet, and further characterize the system. The
planet’s radius is very unusual as M-dwarf field stars rarely have
Neptune-sized transiting planets. The comparatively large radius of
K2-95b is consistent with the other recently discovered cluster planets
